---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="LSCSS Articles"
    description="Articles about modern CSS architecture and Layered Semantic CSS."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Articles</p>

        <h1>
            Articles and essays
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            Longer-form writing about modern CSS architecture, maintainability,
            performance, accessibility, and how CSS methodologies have changed
            as the platform has improved.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Start here
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/articles/methodology-evolution/">
                        CSS methodology evolution
                    </a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Understand why older methodologies emerged, what problems
                    they solved, and where modern CSS changes the trade-offs.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/articles/css-scope-and-lscss/">
                        CSS @scope and LSCSS
                    </a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Explore how @scope fits into Layered Semantic CSS and how it
                    can reduce selector noise without replacing architecture.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Reading paths
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    Methodology thinking
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Start with methodology evolution, then compare LSCSS against
                    BEM, CUBE, and scoped CSS in the comparison guides.
                </p>

                <a href="/comparisons/">
                    View comparisons
                </a>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    Platform features
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Read the @scope article, then work through the modern CSS
                    guides for selectors, nesting, and container queries.
                </p>

                <a href="/modern-css/">
                    View modern CSS guides
                </a>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    Practical adoption
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Pair the articles with migration guidance, examples, and the
                    starter template when applying LSCSS to real projects.
                </p>

                <a href="/migration/">
                    View migration guidance
                </a>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Future article ideas
        </h2>

        <ul>
            <li>Why cascade layers change CSS architecture</li>
            <li>Why specificity problems are often process problems</li>
            <li>How to migrate legacy CSS without a rewrite</li>
            <li>How modern CSS affects BEM-style naming</li>
            <li>Accessibility as part of CSS architecture</li>
            <li>Performance, bundle size, and unused CSS at scale</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</DocsLayout>
